					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So, is there really no way to remove that noise directly in the converted DMC file?<br /></div>No, it is an <em>intrinsic property of the encoding</em>.<br /><br />DPCM will <em>always have noise content at the Nyquist rate unless you intentionally add other noise to displace it</em> and will regardless <em>always have noise content at the sample rate</em>.</div>

